HEADWORD: lawyerbush
<hw>lawyerbush</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A stout-stemmed trailing shrub
(<spn>Rubus cissoides</spn>) of New Zealand that scrambles over other
growth.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> lawyer bush, bush lawyer, <spn>Rubus
cissoides</spn>, <spn>Rubus australis</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

